               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18281023-81-person507">
                  HENRY 
                  WILLIAM CANSDELL
               <interp inst="t18281023-81-person507" type="surname" value="WILLIAM CANSDELL"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18281023-81-person507" type="given" value="HENRY"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18281023-81-person507" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am the son of William Cansdell, of <placeName id="t18281023-81-crimeloc480">Bishopsgate-street Within</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18281023-81-crimeloc480" type="placeName" value="Bishopsgate-street Within"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18281023-81-crimeloc480" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18281023-81-off478 t18281023-81-crimeloc480"></join>. On Saturday evening last, about seven o'clock, I observed five suspicious characters round our door; I watched, and saw the prisoner come out of the office with two bottles of wine - the door is always open; I allowed him to come out, and then seized him; Forrester came up, and took him from me - I found one bottle of wine in his pocket, and the other in his hand; I never lost sight of him.</p>
               <p>Cross-examined by MR. BARRY. Q. Are you quite certain you saw him come out of your door? A. I am - I told the Magistrate so.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18281023-81-person508">
                  DANIEL 
                  FORRESTER
               <interp inst="t18281023-81-person508" type="surname" value="FORRESTER"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18281023-81-person508" type="given" value="DANIEL"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18281023-81-person508" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am an officer. I was passing and secured the prisoner; I took one bottle out of his hand, and the other from his pocket.</p>
               <p>Prisoner's Defence. I was passing the door - a gentleman in a leather-apron asked me to hold the bottles while he stopped for a necessary purpose; I lost sight of him, and as I stood at the door I was taken.</p>
               <p>
                  <rs id="t18281023-81-verdict481" type="verdictDescription">
                     <interp inst="t18281023-81-verdict481" type="verdictCategory" value="guilty"></interp>
               GUILTY
            </rs>. Aged 17.</p>
